1. Inorganic Components of Soil
Soil is a complex mixture of mineral particles, organic matter, water, air, and living organisms. The inorganic
(mineral) fraction constitutes ~45% of soil volume and determines physical properties (texture, structure) and
many chemical properties (CEC, pH buffering, nutrient retention).
1.1 Primary Minerals (Inherited from Parent Rock)
Primary minerals are those that crystallised directly from magma or formed during metamorphism and have not
been chemically altered. They dominate in young, coarse-textured soils (sand and silt fractions).
