1.2 Secondary (Clay) Minerals – Products of Weathering
Clay minerals are phyllosilicates (sheet silicates) formed by chemical weathering of primary minerals. They
dominate the clay fraction (< 2 μm) and are the most chemically reactive component of soil due to their enormous
surface area (up to 800 m²/g) and layer charge.
