2.3 C:N Ratio – Key Decomposition Indicator
Carbon:Nitrogen (C:N) Ratio
The C:N ratio determines whether decomposition results in net N MINERALISATION (release) or N
IMMOBILISATION (uptake by microbes).
• C:N < 20:1 ® Net mineralisation ® excess mineral N (NHnn, NOnn) released to soil ® good for plants
• C:N ~ 20–30:1 ® Balance ® little N released or immobilised
• C:N > 30:1 ® Net immobilisation ® microbes take up available N ® N deficiency in plants
