5. Phosphorus Biogeochemical Cycle
The phosphorus cycle is unique among major nutrient cycles because it has no significant gaseous phase.
Phosphorus moves from rocks (via weathering) through soils and water to organisms, and returns via
decomposition and sedimentation. P is often the limiting nutrient in freshwater ecosystems and many terrestrial
