8. Assertion–Reason Questions
Q1. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): Kaolinite has a much lower cation exchange capacity (CEC) than montmorillonite.
Reason (R): Kaolinite is a 1:1 clay mineral held together by strong hydrogen bonds between layers,
allowing little isomorphous substitution and no interlayer expansion.
(a) Both A and R true; R is correct explanation (b) Both true; R NOT correct explanation (c) A true, R false (d) A
false, R true
4 Answer: (a)
Explanation: Both A and R are true and R correctly explains A. Kaolinite CEC = 2–15 cmol/kg; montmorillonite =
80–120 cmol/kg. Kaolinite's 1:1 structure (T-O) has fixed layers (H-bonding prevents swelling), minimal isomorphous
substitution ® very low permanent charge ® low CEC. Montmorillonite's 2:1 structure has extensive isomorphous
substitution + expands ® high CEC. Select (a).
Q2. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): Biological nitrogen fixation requires an anaerobic microsite even in aerobic organisms
like Azotobacter.
Reason (R): The enzyme nitrogenase, which fixes Nn, is irreversibly inactivated by oxygen.
(a) Both A and R true; R is correct explanation (b) Both true; R NOT correct explanation (c) A true, R false (d) A
false, R true
4 Answer: (a)
Explanation: Both A and R are true and R correctly explains A. Nitrogenase (containing Mo-Fe and Fe-Fe proteins) is
extremely On-sensitive. Azotobacter protects nitrogenase by: (1) very high On consumption rate (respiratory
protection); (2) conformational change of enzyme under On stress. Rhizobium uses leghaemoglobin (pink colour of
nodule) to maintain low On. Select (a).
Q3. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): Phosphorus is more often the limiting nutrient in freshwater lakes, while nitrogen is more
often limiting in marine ecosystems.
Reason (R): Freshwater systems receive P from terrestrial runoff, while marine systems receive N from
atmospheric deposition which is easily utilised.
(a) Both A and R true; R is correct explanation (b) Both true; R NOT correct explanation (c) A true, R false (d) A
false, R true
4 Answer: (b)
Explanation: A is TRUE: This is Liebig's Law applied to aquatic systems. Freshwater is P-limited because external P
loading from agriculture/sewage exceeds N loading relative to algal needs (Redfield ratio ~16N:1P); marine is
N-limited because Nn fixation inputs are lower relative to P. R is PARTIALLY true but NOT the correct/complete
explanation of the limiting nutrient difference. The correct reason relates to Redfield ratio and relative input rates.
Select (b).
Q4. [Assertion–Reason]
Assertion (A): Acid mine drainage (AMD) can have pH as low as 2, lower than most acid rain.
Reason (R): Sulphate-reducing bacteria (SRB) accelerate pyrite oxidation in mine environments,
producing large amounts of HnSOn.
(a) Both A and R true; R is correct explanation (b) Both true; R NOT correct explanation (c) A true, R false (d) A
false, R true
4 Answer: (c)
